headline: General Mills keeps annual outlook as North America demand softens
summary: General Mills reaffirmed its annual targets of adjusted profit declining 10% to 15% and organic net sales ranging from down 1% to up 1%. The first-quarter results underscore how tough the current environment is for food makers, who need to invest heavily to reignite volume growth, as consumers remain price-conscious but expect benefits such as added protein and distinctive flavors, Consumer Edge analyst Connor Rattigan said. Shares were down 1% in choppy early morning trading.
